citations:
    citation-adwd-melisandre:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "Melisandre"
            text_from_source: "The glamor, aye... I feel it when I sleep. Warm against my skin, even through the iron. Soft as a woman's kiss. Your kiss. But sometimes in my dreams it starts to burn, and your lips turn into teeth."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Melisandre's sole POV chapter. She receives visions of Jon Snow surrounded by skulls — foreshadowing his assassination. She sees the wooden face and the boy with a wolf's face (likely the Night's King and Bran Warg). She sends for 'Rattleshirt' (actually Mance Rayder glamored to appear as the Lord of Bones by a ruby on a black iron fetter). The glamor disguises Mance as Rattleshirt, with Rattleshirt presumably sent south glamored as Mance to be burned. Jon Snow later sends this disguised Mance south as 'Abel the singer' to Winterfell. Melisandre also seeks a 'grey girl on a dying horse' in the flames — she believes this is Arya Stark fleeing (she is actually glimpsing Alys Karstark). References: Devan Seaworth (Davos's son, Melisandre's page). Her birth name is revealed as 'Melony' and she was Lot Seven at the red temple — she was once a slave."
